---
description: TypeScript strictness rules — no any, explicit types, Zod validation
globs: **/*.ts, **/*.tsx
alwaysApply: false
---
No `any` — ever. Use `unknown` and narrow it.
All function parameters and return types must be explicit.
Use interface for object shapes, type for unions/intersections.
Avoid type assertions (as X) unless you explain why in a comment.
Enums over magic strings for status/role/type values.
Zod for all runtime validation and schema inference.
No `var` — always `const` or `let`.
